import {
  GridItem,
  Text,
  Center,
  Stack,
  Heading,
  Image,
  Box,
  Container,
  Avatar,
  Spacer,
} from '@chakra-ui/react'
import React from 'react'

const AspectJesse = () => {
  return (
    <GridItem colStart={1} colSpan={4}>
      <Container bg={'blackAlpha.300'} width={'xl'} rounded={'md'} p={3}>
        <Heading>
          Religion and Ritual Life
          <Avatar src={''} alt={'Author'} name='Jesse Kuehl' bg='teal.400' />
        </Heading>
        <Text fontSize={'xl'} color='whiteAlpha.700'>
          Classic Period Maya Religion
        </Text>
        <Center>
          <Image
            m={3}
            alignSelf={'center'}
            transform='scale(1.0)'
            src={
              'https://c4.wallpaperflare.com/wallpaper/709/147/694/stars-architecture-maya-civilization-pyramid-wallpaper-preview.jpg'
            }
            alt='maya religion'
            objectFit={'contain'}
            transition='0.3s ease-in-out'
            height='fill'
          />
        </Center>
        There are many benefits to a joint design and development system. Not
        only does it bring benefits to the design team, but it also brings
        benefits to engineering teams. It makes sure that our experiences have a
        consistent look and feel, not just in our design specs, but in
        production
      </Container>
    </GridItem>
  )
}

export default AspectJesse
